The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, October 31, 2002  Corporate Briefs																								 Coca-Cola Indias carbonated soft drinks (CSD) sales recorded a 30 per cent volume growth in the quarter ended September 30 compared with 26 per cent in the previous quarter ended June 30. Correspondingly, the companys all-India market share in the CSD category at the end of August 31 increased by 2.2 per cent. Kinleys (Coca-Colas packaged water brand) market share, according to the latest ORG-MARG National Retail Sales Audit grew by 1.5 per cent to 36.6 per cent against Bisleris 31.4 per cent and Aquafinas 12.5 per cent at the end of August 31.																								 Confederation of Indian Industry (CII) will organise a conference on IT enabled services (ITeS) on December 12 in Calcutta. The national seminar will address issues of the ITeS industry and project the eastern states of the country as a possible destination for ITeS investments. 																								 Encyclopaedia Britannica has released its 2003 Ultimate Reference Suite. The product is available on CD-ROM and DVD for Windows and Macintosh computers. 																								 IBM India has launched self-managing DB 2 version 8 software to help companies simplify and automate tasks associated with maintaining databases. 																								 Sun F amp;C Mutual Fund has declared a dividend of 0.75 per cent (or Re 0.0750 per unit on face value of Rs 10) under the monthly dividend plan. 																								 HDFC Bank has waived off interest charges on all spends and cash advances for new customers of its international silver and gold cards for a period of 90 days from date of purchase. It is also offering free cards under a special balance transfer facility. These schemes are open to customers signed up between October and December 2002. 																								 Tektronix has launched a set of signal integrity measurement and analysis tools for digital engineers developing fast serial-based systems and computing, networking, and communications devices.																								 Cognizant Technology Solutions Corporation has completed the previously announced transfer of Silverlines American Express practice to Cognizant. The terms of the transaction were not disclosed.																								 Sun Microsystems will join the Web Services Interoperability Organisation (WS-I) as a contributing member. The WS-I was founded as an effort to promote Web services interoperability across platforms, applications and programming languages.																								 Van Heusen has launched the Inferno range of shirts, a release said. ADVERTISEMENT
